courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, participants should be able to:

1. Employ a critical lens of multiculturalism to address the learning and teaching issues in early years;
2. Effectively apply culturally relevant pedagogy in promoting positive engagement of both mainstream and non-mainstream young children from early years to primary schooling;
3. Demonstrate intercultural competence in working with parents from diverse cultural backgrounds;
4. Critically analyse the policy documents and provision relating to enhancing multicultural early years education;
5. Foster an equitable and inclusive learning environment for holistic engagement of early years within the Hong Kong context.

At the end of this course, students are expected to:

1. Understand and perform the role of a professional kindergarten teachers in learning and teaching;
2. Organize integrated and developmentally appropriate activities to enrich children’s holistic development in the Hong Kong kindergarten context;
3. Demonstrate competence in designing, implementing and evaluating meaningful and appropriate learning experiences for young children.

4. Apply basic strategies to manage the kindergarten classrooms effectively.

At the end of this course, students are expected to:

1. Understand and perform the role of a reflective practitioner in early childhood education;
2. Organize and reflect on integrated and developmentally appropriate activities to enrich children’s holistic development in the Hong Kong kindergarten context;
3. Demonstrate competence in observing and assessing children’s learning experience and reflecting on their own teaching performance.

4. Apply advanced strategies to manage the kindergarten classrooms in order to facilitate their effective teaching.
